      "blocks": {
        "faq-1": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What does onboarding look like?",
            "answer": "<p>We start with a free discovery call, followed by a financial review of your current books and tax situation. Within two weeks, we present a clear plan with transparent pricing and begin implementing systems.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-2": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do you structure your fees?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients are on a fixed monthly retainer that covers bookkeeping, tax planning, and advisory. Tax preparation and audit services are quoted separately. We always discuss fees before any work begins.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-3": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do you communicate with clients?",
            "answer": "<p>Every client has a dedicated account manager available by phone, email, and video call. You'll receive monthly financial reports and we schedule quarterly strategy reviews throughout the year.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-4": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What software do you work with?",
            "answer": "<p>We're proficient in QuickBooks Online, Xero, FreshBooks, and most major accounting platforms. We'll recommend the best fit for your business and handle the migration if needed.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-5": {
          "type": "item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "When should I start tax planning?",
            "answer": "<p>Now. The earlier in the year we begin, the more strategies are available. We recommend engaging at least six months before year-end, but year-round clients see the greatest savings.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "blocksOrder": ["faq-1", "faq-2", "faq-3", "faq-4", "faq-5"]
